cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.MM

This paper deals with clustering geo-tagged records on social media based on textual descriptions, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) to process the textual data. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new density-based clustering algorithm, which involves techniques from database systems (DB) and machine learning (MM), making cs.DB and cs.MM likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of fuzzy clustering, which is a technique from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (MM), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
